cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.COM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.GT (Game Theory): The paper proposes a noncooperative game theoretic approach to incentivize spectrum sharing among providers. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper deals with the allocation and sharing of radio spectrum resources among commercial service providers. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the use of regulatory power to improve and facilitate sharing of radio spectrum resources. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper may touch upon security concerns related to sharing of radio spectrum resources among providers. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society): The paper may discuss the impact of regulatory policies on the market and competition among service providers.
